        <updateDate>2022-01-07T16:05:09Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Keep Innovation in America Act</strong></p> <p>This bill expands the definition of <em>broker</em>, for purposes of tax information reporting, to include any person who (for consideration) stands ready in the ordinary course of a trade or business to effect sales of digital assets at the direction of their customers. It also provides for reporting requirements for <em>digital assets</em> (i.e., any digital representation of value that is recorded on a cryptographically secured distributed ledger). </p> <p>The bill requires a study and a report on the treatment of digital assets as cash for purposes of reporting requirements for cash payments of more than $10,000.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
